Governor Paterson's appointment of Kirsten Gillibrand to fill Secretary Clinton's seat in the United States Senate is praised by President Obama. He believes that Gillibrand will continue Clinton's service to the people of New York and the country. Gillibrand has been a strong advocate for transparency and government reform throughout her career. She has also worked to strengthen public and private partnerships to invest in infrastructure and New York's economy. President Obama has confidence in Gillibrand's integrity, character, and dedication to public service, especially during challenging times.